elements.title: Freddie Lish
elements.contents: ... that American-born Freddie Lish called playing for the Thai national basketball team, "my dream ever since I found out my mom was born in Thailand"?

elements.title: the 1955 election
elements.contents: ... that Pakistani prime minister Mohammad Ali Bogra opposed the 1955 election to protect his political position?

elements.title: J. C. Walter Jr.
elements.contents: ... that nine days after his heart transplant, J. C. Walter Jr. merged his company Houston Oil & Minerals with Tenneco, then retired to his ranch and shortly after founded Walter Oil & Gas?

elements.title: Lope Martín
elements.contents: ... that during his final known voyage, Lope Martín overthrew two captains before being marooned on Ujelang Atoll?

elements.title: a Japanese governor
elements.contents: ... that a Japanese governor wore a pregnancy simulation suit to encourage men to help out their wives at home?

elements.title: shooting of Eileen Quinn
elements.contents: ... that the shooting of Eileen Quinn was referenced in the poetry of W. B. Yeats?

elements.title: Victor L. King
elements.contents: ... that Victor L. King employed only black people from the South in 1917 at his new chemical plant in New Jersey to "prevent the entrance into the organization of any enemy aliens" during World War I?

elements.title: delivered the longest recorded individual speech
elements.contents: ... that Cory Booker delivered the longest recorded individual speech in United States Senate history while protesting the second presidency of Donald Trump?
